          "content": "## Refined Implementation Design\n\n### **1. Enhanced proceed_to_phase Validation Logic**\n```typescript\n// In proceed_to_phase handler:\nif (conversationState.requireReviewsBeforePhaseTransition) {\n  const transition = getTransitionConfig(currentPhase, target_phase);\n  \n  if (transition.review_perspectives && transition.review_perspectives.length > 0) {\n    // Workflow-defined review perspectives exist\n    if (args.review_state === 'pending') {\n      // Provide the LLM with review perspectives and prompts for conduct_review\n      const reviewData = {\n        perspectives: transition.review_perspectives.map(p => p.perspective),\n        prompts: transition.review_perspectives.map(p => p.prompt)\n      };\n      throw new Error(`Review is required before proceeding to ${target_phase}. Use conduct_review with: ${JSON.stringify(reviewData)}`);\n    }\n  } else {\n    // No workflow-defined perspectives - fallback to user review\n    if (args.review_state === 'pending') {\n      throw new Error(`No automated review perspectives defined. Please ask the user to manually review the ${currentPhase} phase artifacts before proceeding to ${target_phase}.`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### **2. Stateless conduct_review Tool**\n```typescript\ninterface ConductReviewArgs {\n  perspectives: string[];           // e.g., [\"architecture\", \"security\"]\n  prompts: string[];               // Corresponding review prompts\n  artifacts_context: string;       // Context about what to review\n  review_type?: 'llm' | 'checklist' | 'user_guided';\n}\n\ninterface ConductReviewResult {\n  perspectives_reviewed: string[];\n  findings: Array<{\n    perspective: string;\n    issues: string[];\n    recommendations: string[];\n    severity: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high';\n  }>;\n  overall_assessment: 'approved' | 'needs_changes' | 'rejected';\n  summary: string;\n}\n```\n\n### **3. Workflow YAML Schema (unchanged but clarified)**\n```yaml\nstates:\n  explore:\n    transitions:\n      - trigger: \"exploration_complete\"\n        to: \"plan\"\n        review_perspectives:\n          - perspective: \"architecture\"\n            prompt: \"Review the exploration findings from an architectural perspective. Consider scalability, maintainability, and technical debt implications. Focus on the technology choices and system design decisions made during exploration.\"\n          - perspective: \"security\"\n            prompt: \"Evaluate potential security considerations based on the exploration findings. Look for authentication, authorization, data protection, and vulnerability concerns.\"\n```\n\n### **4. Example Flow Scenarios**\n\n**Scenario A: Workflow-defined perspectives**\n```\nLLM: calls proceed_to_phase({ target_phase: \"plan\", review_state: \"pending\" })\nSystem: Error with review data: \"Use conduct_review with: {perspectives: ['architecture', 'security'], prompts: ['Review from...', 'Evaluate security...']}\"\n\nLLM: calls conduct_review({ \n  perspectives: [\"architecture\", \"security\"], \n  prompts: [\"Review from...\", \"Evaluate security...\"],\n  artifacts_context: \"Exploration phase completed with technology stack decisions and system design approach\"\n})\nSystem: Returns review results\n\nLLM: calls proceed_to_phase({ target_phase: \"plan\", review_state: \"performed\" })\nSystem: Success\n```\n\n**Scenario B: No workflow perspectives (fallback)**\n```\nLLM: calls proceed_to_phase({ target_phase: \"plan\", review_state: \"pending\" })\nSystem: Error: \"No automated review perspectives defined. Please ask the user to manually review the explore phase artifacts.\"\n\nLLM: \"Before we proceed to planning, could you please review the exploration work we've completed? [presents artifacts and asks for feedback]\"\nUser: \"Looks good, proceed\"\n\nLLM: calls proceed_to_phase({ target_phase: \"plan\", review_state: \"performed\" })\nSystem: Success\n```\n\nThis design is much cleaner because:\n\n1. **Stateless conduct_review**: No dependencies on workflow files or conversation state\n2. **Clear data flow**: All review data flows through parameters\n3. **Flexible fallback**: Graceful degradation to user review when no automation available\n4. **Error-driven guidance**: Error messages guide the LLM on exactly what to do\n\nShould I continue exploring the implementation details of the `conduct_review` tool, particularly how it would handle different review types (LLM vs checklist vs user-guided)?",
